          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Understanding your property's soil type explains why neighbors experience different problems. A home in Woodbridge on clay soil needs aggressive exterior drainage and flexible waterproofing membranes. A Thornhill home on sandy soil requires robust weeping tile systems to handle rapid water movement. Generic waterproofing solutions fail because they ignore these local conditions.
          </p>
        </div>
