          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 mt-8">
            Foundation Crack Epidemics
          </h3>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Vaughan homes built during winter months experience higher rates of foundation cracking due to concrete poured in suboptimal temperatures. Proper cold-weather concrete requires heated aggregate, insulated blankets during curing, and extended cure times. These precautions cost money and delay construction schedules. Many builders skipped them, resulting in concrete with reduced strength and durability.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Horizontal cracks along mortar joints in poured concrete foundations typically indicate settlement or soil pressure issues. Vertical cracks from floor to ceiling suggest temperature stress or improper concrete mix. Step cracks in concrete block foundations point to differential settlement. All these cracks provide entry points for water. Even hairline cracks invisible to the naked eye can channel significant water volume during heavy rainfall.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 mt-8">
            The Luxury Home Illusion
          </h3>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Vaughan's luxury subdivisions — Sonoma Heights, The Estates of Credit Ridge, Kleinburg Crown Estates — command premium prices but often feature the same basement waterproofing shortcuts as mid-market homes. You paid for granite countertops and hardwood stairs, not proper foundation waterproofing. Builders allocate budgets to visible finishes that justify high prices while cutting corners on hidden infrastructure like waterproofing and drainage.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            DrySpace has waterproofed $2 million+ Vaughan homes with foundation systems identical to $600,000 homes in adjacent neighborhoods. The luxury premium bought you square footage and finishes, not superior construction quality. This reality becomes clear when basement water issues emerge, and you discover your million-dollar home has the same inadequate damp-proof coating as the builder's entry-level model.
          </p>
        </div>
