      <!-- Section 4: Tarion Warranty -->
      <section id="tarion-warranty" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">
          4. Tarion Warranty & Your Waterproofing Options
        </h2>

        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Every new home in Ontario includes Tarion Warranty Corporation coverage, which provides specific protection for basement waterproofing defects. Understanding these warranty periods and coverage limitations determines whether you can force the builder to fix problems or must pay for repairs yourself. Many Vaughan homeowners miss critical warranty deadlines because they don't understand how Tarion works.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 mt-8">
            Tarion Coverage Periods for Waterproofing
          </h3>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Tarion divides defects into categories with different coverage periods. Basement water penetration falls under multiple categories depending on severity and cause. Year One coverage includes any defect in materials or work. This means if water enters your basement during the first year of ownership, it's automatically a warranty issue. You must report it on your Year-End form submitted 30-90 days before your first anniversary of possession.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Year Two coverage becomes more limited, protecting only specific items listed in Tarion's warranty guidelines. Minor water seepage may not qualify after Year One. Major Structural Defects receive seven years of coverage, including foundation waterproofing failures that result from construction defects. However, proving a leak qualifies as "major structural" requires documentation and often disputes with Tarion.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-cyan-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-500 p-6 my-8 rounded-r-lg">
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-cyan-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-900 mb-2">Critical Warranty Action</h3>
                <p class="text-cyan-800">
                  If you notice any moisture, dampness, or water in your basement during Year One, report it immediately on your Year-End form. Even if it seems minor, document it. This creates a warranty record that protects you if problems worsen in Years 2-7. Without Year One documentation, Tarion often denies later claims.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 mt-8">
            What Tarion Covers (and Doesn't)
          </h3>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Tarion covers defects in construction materials and workmanship. This includes foundations that leak due to inadequate waterproofing, missing weeping tiles, improper grading by the builder, and foundation cracks caused by construction defects. Tarion does not cover damage from homeowner modifications, lack of maintenance, landscaping changes that affect drainage, or normal wear and tear.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The gray area involves determining whether water entry results from construction defects or external factors. Builders routinely blame homeowners for grading problems even when original site conditions were defective. Tarion often sides with builders in ambiguous situations. You need documentation — photos of original grading, records of maintenance, evidence that you didn't alter drainage — to win these disputes.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-slate-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4">Tarion Waterproofing Coverage Timeline</h4>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-slate-200">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Time Period</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Coverage Type</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">What's Covered</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Action Required</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-200 bg-white">
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">Year 1</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">Comprehensive</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">Any water penetration, dampness, or moisture</td>
