            Basement waterproofing costs in Vaughan depend on multiple factors: foundation perimeter length, depth, soil conditions, site access, and whether you need exterior or interior solutions. Understanding these cost drivers helps you budget accurately and evaluate contractor quotes. Here's what professional waterproofing actually costs in Vaughan in 2026.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 mt-8">
            Exterior Waterproofing: The Comprehensive Solution
          </h3>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Exterior waterproofing involves excavating around your foundation to the footing level, installing new waterproofing membrane, replacing or installing weeping tiles, and backfilling with proper drainage materials. This approach addresses the root cause of basement water problems by preventing water from reaching your foundation walls. It's the most expensive option but provides the most reliable long-term protection.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Vaughan exterior waterproofing costs range from $155 to $280 per linear foot in 2026. This wide range reflects variations in foundation depth, soil conditions, and site complexity. A typical Vaughan home with 100-120 linear feet of foundation perimeter pays $12,000-$28,000 for complete exterior waterproofing. Luxury homes with deeper foundations, challenging soil conditions, or site access constraints can exceed $40,000 for comprehensive exterior work.
